<step1>
<ptxt>OPERATION</ptxt>
<step2>
<ptxt>Evaporative Emission Control System</ptxt>
<step3>
<ptxt>Based on the signals from various sensors, the ECM opens and closes the VSV (for EVAP). Thus, it controls the purge flow of evaporative emissions (HC) in the charcoal canister sub-assembly in accordance with the engine conditions.</ptxt>
</step3>
</step2>
</step1>
